During extraction of gold, the gold ore is treated with aqueous KCN solution as shown by the equations (not balanced) below to get compound X which is further reduced by Zn to obtain compound Y and metallic gold. Identify X and Y .
$\begin{aligned}
& \text { Gold ore }+\mathrm{CN}^{-}+\mathrm{H}_2 \mathrm{O}+\mathrm{O}_2 \rightarrow[\mathrm{X}]+\mathrm{OH}^{-} \ldots \ldots \text{(i)}\\
& {[\mathrm{X}]+\mathrm{Zn} \rightarrow[\mathrm{Y}]+\mathrm{Au}} \qquad \qquad \qquad \qquad \qquad \ldots \ldots \text{(ii)}
\end{aligned}$
